post_text:
‚ÄúThe onset of the pandemic disrupted a lot of capstone events, but despite all the negativity, there are moments that we can all be proud of‚Äîwhether it be finding hope in what we‚Äôve done during quarantine or the surge of activism and accountability around the world. It‚Äôs these moments that I choose to define my senior year by.‚Äù

Ahead of this weekend‚Äôs commencements, we connected with over a dozen graduating seniors selected by Valley High School administration, staff, and teachers as prime-time students who best showcased the "Valley Standard" through its four A's‚ÄîAcademics, Activities, Arts, and Athletics‚Äîduring their high school and WDMCS careers. Dive into their personal narratives illustrating their journeys. Read how COVID-19 abruptly altered the closing chapters to their senior years and what lies ahead in their futures, told by none other than the students themselves.

shared_text:
WDMCS Nutrition
May 8 at 4:55 PM ¬∑

HOW AWESOME IS THIS? Fairmeadows Elementary (WDMCS) fifth-grader Audrey H. always works hard to get 100% during the school's Spelling Challenge, which is an annual fundraiser for each grade level. Due to #COVID19, however, the challenge was canceled.

Audrey was inspired to still participate in the Spelling Challenge on her own as a way to challenge herself, and she collected pledges to donate to WDMCS Nutrition Services. After long study sessions, Audrey scored 100%! With the help of her family and friends, she raised $665 that will be used for additional freezer meals for our families amid the COVID-19 crisis.

THANK YOU, Audrey, for your determination, grace, and generous donation that will impact our district! #TigersTogether #weareWDMCS

WDMCSFOUNDATION.ORG
West Des Moines Community Schools Foundation : News & Events : COVID-19 Student Support

WDMCS Foundation
May 5 at 5:44 PM ¬∑

Today is Teacher Appreciation Day and we thank them for their heroic efforts in making the switch to online curriculum so students can continue to learn during the COVID-19 crisis. However, teachers share our concern that many at-risk students are falling behind because they don't have access to technology or even proper nutrition. The West Des Moines Community Schools Foundation has set up special donation categories for TECHNOLOGY and FOOD. The funds raised will help create technology access for all students and support the district's Grab 'N Go meals for qualifying families. Show your appreciation for our teachers by making a difference in the lives of their most vulnerable students. #makeanimpact #theyarethefuture

Carter won the 2019 Academy Award for "Best Costume Design" for her work on the film "Black Panther" and made history as the first African American to win in that category. post_text: Congratulations to WDMCS grad Adam Meyer on being named the new Juilliard provost! #wearewdmcs
shared_text:
The Juilliard School
February 12 at 4:01 PM ¬∑

We are excited to announce that alumnus Adam Meyer has been appointed as provost, succeeding Ara Guzelimian, who is stepping down this July following 13 years of incomparable service to Juilliard as our provost and dean. Adam joined the Juilliard administrative team in 2011 and currently serves as director of the Music Division and deputy dean of the College. With his appointment, President Damian Woetzel said, ‚ÄúAdam brings to this new role a profound dedication to excellence and to supporting faculty and students with a caring expertise that inspires trust and underlies his demonstrated leadership.‚Äù Read the full press release: https://buff.ly/39urXIi
